    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-06-17T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-06-17T22:00:00-05:00" n="511"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d511">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/22826: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Ciudad Juarez</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dow</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-17T21:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 17, 1919, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received June 18, 9 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Unofficial reports indicate about 225 Villistas were killed in or near Juarez
                    June 15 and 16. American troops killed about 100. They brought to United States
                    100 horses of bandits. Remaining 125 Villistas killed by Mexican troops under
                    General Francisco Gonzales. Have today urged latter to send immediately troops
                    to Casas Grandes. This place should have at least 500 men to protect 500
                    Americans in that vicinity. Juarez quiet today and no important ill feeling
                    against the Americans on part of Mexican people there. Embassy advised.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dow</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
